@startuml
title ImpulsaEdu - Implementation Diagram

actor Browser
actor "Admin / Operators" as Admin

node "GKE Cluster" as GKE {
  node "Ingress (NGINX)" as Ingress

  node "Frontend (Next.js)" as Frontend {
    [frontend]
  }

  node "Auth Service (Fastify)" as Auth {
    [auth-service]
  }

  node "API Service (Fastify)" as API {
    [api-service]
  }
}

database "PostgreSQL (impulsa)" as DB
cloud "Cloud SQL (optional)" as CloudDB

Browser --> Ingress : HTTP(S)
Ingress --> Frontend : /*  (Next.js public + admin UI)
Ingress --> Auth : /auth/*
Ingress --> API  : /api/v1/*

Frontend --> Auth : POST /auth/login (httpOnly cookie)
Frontend --> API  : GET/POST /api/v1/* (cookie or Bearer)

API ..> Auth : validates JWT locally (shared JWT_SECRET)

Auth --> DB : users, refresh_tokens
API  --> DB : donors, schools, donations, needs, items, contacts, audit_logs

note right of API
  - Updates `schools.progress` on donation state changes
  - Updates `schools.goal` when needs change
  - Enforces state transitions (422 on invalid)
end note

Admin --> Auth : manage users
Admin --> API  : manage donors / schools / donations

' If using managed DB, point services to Cloud SQL
API --> CloudDB : read/write
Auth --> CloudDB : read/write

note bottom
  Deployment: Deploy to GKE with Deployments (frontend/auth/api),
  Ingress routes, Secrets for `JWT_SECRET`, and a managed Postgres.
end note

@enduml
